    <string name="legal_editor_title">Publisher</string>
    <string name="legal_editor_content">The Telo Application is published by Dotshell. Dotshell is not affiliated with Réseau Mistral, RD TPM or the Toulon Provence Méditerranée Metropolis. For any questions, please refer to the contact details provided in the Application.\n</string>
    <string name="legal_object_title">Purpose</string>
    <string name="legal_object_content">These Terms of Use define the conditions of access and use of the Telo Application (hereinafter "the Application"). Using the Application implies acceptance of these terms.\n</string>
    <string name="legal_desc_title">Application Description</string>
    <string name="legal_desc_content">The Application helps the user navigate the Mistral network (Toulon and surrounding area) through search and planning tools. Third-party sources are listed in the "Credits" page.\n</string>
    <string name="legal_permissions_title">Permissions</string>
    <string name="legal_permissions_content">The Application may request the following permissions based on technical needs:\n• Location: To display nearby stops and center the map (processed locally).\n• Network/Internet: To display map tiles.\n</string>
    <string name="legal_privacy_title">Data Processing and Privacy</string>
    <string name="legal_privacy_content">Telo is designed according to the principle of data protection by design.\n\n5.1. Exclusive local storage\nYour favorite stops, your preferences and your trip history are stored exclusively locally on your device. Dotshell has no access to this information. You can delete this history at any time from the "Privacy" screen.\n\n5.2. Offline operation\nJourney search and schedule lookup run entirely on your device, from data bundled with the application. Your itineraries are computed on your device and never leave it; only the features described in 5.3 (map tiles, address search, walking paths) use the network.\n\n5.3. Network access\nThe Application network exchanges are limited to:\n• map tiles (provided by OpenFreeMap and ESRI), with no personal identifier;\n• address and place search: the text typed in the search bar is sent to the Photon geocoding service (komoot GmbH, Germany), based on OpenStreetMap, in order to turn it into a geographic position;\n• walking-path display: the start and end coordinates of the walk (for example your position or a searched address) are sent to the OSRM pedestrian router (FOSSGIS e.V., Germany) in order to draw the path taken on the map.\nThese requests are necessary for the service you request (GDPR article 6(1)(b)), encrypted (HTTPS) and carry no account, cookie or advertising identifier: only your IP address and the application identity accompany them, as with any Internet request. Dotshell has no access to these requests and keeps nothing from them. Offline, address search is unavailable and walking paths are estimated locally, with no transmission.\n\n5.4. No collection, no resale\nDotshell does not collect your data and does not sell any data to advertisers or data brokers.\n</string>
    <string name="legal_liability_title">Liability</string>
    <string name="legal_liability_content">Information (schedules, disruptions) is provided for guidance only. Dotshell declines all responsibility in the event of inaccuracies in data from third parties or unavailability of the transport network.\n</string>
    <string name="legal_ip_title">Intellectual Property</string>
    <string name="legal_ip_content">The Application\'s source code is distributed under the GPL-3.0 license. Trademarks and logos of transport networks remain the property of their respective owners.\n</string>
    <string name="legal_updates_title">Updates</string>
    <string name="legal_updates_content">Dotshell reserves the right to modify these Terms. The applicable version is the one available in the Application at the time of its use.\n</string>
    <string name="credits_transport_data_title">Transport Data</string>
    <string name="credits_transport_data_content">The transport data used in the application comes from the GTFS (General Transit Feed Specification) dataset of the Réseau Mistral published by the Toulon Provence Méditerranée Metropolis on the transport.data.gouv.fr platform, under the Licence Ouverte v2.0.\n\nThe geographic positions and names of stops, line contents, schedules and the geographic paths of the bus, sea shuttle and Mont Faron cable car lines all come from this GTFS file. This data is manually updated by developers and undergoes pre-processing before being bundled into the application. No data is modified: only its organization is transformed for faster processing, and the application then works fully offline for journey search and schedules.\n\nLine badges are generated from the network's official colors contained in this same GTFS file.</string>
    <string name="credits_cartography_title">Mapping</string>
    <string name="credits_cartography_content">Map data is provided by MapLibre and OpenStreetMaps.\n\nMap styles (namely Positron, Dark Matter, OSM Bright, and Liberty) are provided by OpenMapTiles. The application uses the Map Tiler Positron (Light) theme by default.\n\nSatellite view tiles come from ESRI World Imagery.</string>
    <string name="credits_development_title">Development</string>
    <string name="credits_development_content">The application is developed independently by Dotshell under the GPL-3.0 license. Telo is not affiliated with Réseau Mistral, RD TPM or the Toulon Provence Méditerranée Metropolis.\n\nThe source code is available on Dotshell's GitHub page at the following repositories: telo-kmp for the application source code (Android and iOS), plus raptor-gtfs-pipeline and raptor-kt for the RAPTOR routing system.\n\nAny contribution is open to the community.\n\nFor more information, go to dotshell.eu.</string>
